# Part 2

## Describe a famous person you would like to meet.

One famous person I’d really like to meet is Jensen Huang, who is the founder and CEO of NVIDIA. He’s widely regarded as one of the most influential figures in the AI industry, especially because NVIDIA’s GPUs have become the foundation of modern artificial intelligence and deep learning technologies.

I first got to know him through technology news and AI-related videos online. As a computer science student who is deeply interested in AI and robotics, I often read about breakthroughs in machine learning, and his name appears almost everywhere. What impressed me most was not only his technical vision, but also his leadership style and persistence. He transformed NVIDIA from a gaming hardware company into one of the world’s most valuable AI companies, which is honestly inspiring.

If I had the chance, I’d love to meet him at an international AI conference, such as NVIDIA GTC or another global tech summit. I think that kind of environment would make the conversation more meaningful because people there are passionate about innovation and future technologies.

The main reason I want to meet him is that I’d love to ask him about the future of AI and how students like me should prepare for it. I’d also like to know how he makes long-term decisions in such a fast-changing industry. In addition, I really admire his mindset. Even after becoming extremely successful, he still seems energetic, curious and willing to take risks. I think meeting him would motivate me to work harder on my own projects and perhaps dream bigger about my future career in AI.

---

